Project Synopsis
Project Title:
Personal Expense Tracker & Budget Analyzer
Project Description:
A menu-driven console-based Python application that allows users to efficiently track their daily income and expenses, set category-wise budgets, and analyze their spending habits. The system provides useful insights such as monthly summaries, budget vs actual spending comparison, and financial reports.
This project is developed using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) and demonstrates excellent skills in file handling using CSV files, exception handling, and clean code practices.
Objective:
To build a robust and user-friendly personal finance management system that helps users maintain financial discipline and make informed spending decisions.
Key Functionalities:

Add new transaction (Income / Expense)
View all transactions
Search transactions
Update a transaction
Delete a transaction
Set monthly budget for different categories
View budget analysis (Spent vs Budget)
Generate financial summaries (Total Income, Total Expense, Savings, etc.)
Filter transactions (by month, category, type)
Show total record count and basic statistics

Technical Stack:

Python (OOP Approach)
CSV files for data storage (transactions.csv and budgets.csv)
csv module for file operations
Strong Exception Handling and Input Validation

File Structure:

transactions.csv → Stores all income and expense records
budgets.csv → Stores monthly budget limits by category